item.title: Help again (not same problem)
item.dc:creator: @howz_my_aim howz my aim
item.description:
@howz_my_aim wrote:

@echo off
@TITLE Project Reality
if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit

Thats my compiler and it says i dont have java installed when i know for a fact i do

item.title: Help again (not same problem)
item.dc:creator: @superpersonxd superpersonxd
item.description:
@superpersonxd wrote:

Well for your compiler, or client to work they both have to be leading in the right file path for “JRE” and “JDK”. For instance on a common 32*bit computer using win7 and C:\ as the primary drive the file path would be “C:\Program Files\Java\jre6\ (and so on)”
so open your run/batch with notepad and change the path to your jre/jdk
